U-Boot for ODROID-C2
====================

ODROID-C2 is a single board computer manufactured by Hardkernel
Co. Ltd with the following specifications:

 - Amlogic S905 ARM Cortex-A53 quad-core SoC @ 2GHz
 - ARM Mali 450 GPU
 - 2GB DDR3 SDRAM
 - Gigabit Ethernet
 - HDMI 2.0 4K/60Hz display
 - 40-pin GPIO header
 - 4 x USB 2.0 Host, 1 x USB OTG
 - eMMC, microSD
 - Infrared receiver

Schematics are available on the manufacturer website.

Currently the u-boot port supports the following devices:
 - serial
 - eMMC, microSD
 - Ethernet

u-boot compilation
==================

 > export ARCH=arm
 > export CROSS_COMPILE=aarch64-none-elf-
 > make odroid-c2_defconfig
 > make

Image creation
==============

After compiling is done, finaly boot image is created in
'board/amlogic/odroid-c2/bin/u-boot.bin.signed', and it can be
flashed with a script as below.

 $ sudo board/amlogic/odroid-c2/bin/sd_fusing.sh <dev/your_sd_device>
